FBIS4-31138 "dreeu108_k_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 CROATIA Finance Minister Announces Zero Inflation Rate Finance Minister Announces Zero Inflation Rate LD0306215994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in English 2103 GMT 3 Jun 94 LD0306215994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network English BFN [Text] Finance Minister Zoran Jasic, speaking in Split today, stated that the first phase of the goverment's stabilization program has achieved its most important goal, that being the reduction of the inflation rate to zero. Nevertheless, reports unconfirmed by the ministry state that the prices of agricultural products have risen around 20 percent. Minister Jasic announced that negotiations with the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank could result in loans of $128 million for reconstruction, although IMF and World Bank sources say the talks are continuing.
